Cell.Text: Who in the blazes are you?! Can't you see I'm busy?
Why should I tell you? I don't even know who you are.
Hmph, maybe. Been difficult trusting people lately, they think I'm crazy.
Exploring, huh? Most folks think this place isn't worth the effort.

Cell.Text: Ask most of the folks around here and they'd agree with you.

Node.Caption: DLC2RR03CresciusIntroBranchTopic01c: It's dangerous here for an old man.

Cell.Text: A secret the East Empire Company swept under the rug two centuries ago. | It killed my great-grandfather, and left Raven Rock with a worthless and tainted mine.

Node.Caption: DLC2RR03CresciusIntroExtBranchTopic: What sort of a secret would be hidden here?

Cell.Text: [S] But mark my words, these mines hold a secret that could put Raven Rock back on the map.
Gratian Caerellius. He spent his entire life exploring ancient ruins across Tamriel and he died in these very mines almost 200 years ago.
You never heard of them? | They're the largest trading company in Tamriel, originally chartered by the Emperor of Cyrodiil himself.
East Empire Company called it "a terrible accident," claiming that he was lost in a rockfall, but I know better.

My wife and I were cleaning out our home, and we came across some of my great-grandfather's things locked in an old chest. | I found an unsent letter he'd written to the East Empire Company, and a key.

It describes a discovery that was made in the mine by some of the diggers. They wanted Gratian to take a closer look. | The East Empire Company must have felt it was of great value, as they locked that section of the mine off from everyone else.
It is. Well, I assume it is. I haven't been able to find the entrance.

Node.Caption: DLC2RR03CresciusIntroExtBranchTopic05: The key is to the locked section?

Cell.Text: Now you're starting to sound like everyone else.

Node.Caption: DLC2RR03CresciusIntroExtBranchTopic06a: This is hardly proof of anything.

Cell.Text: [S] I'm telling you... there's something big down there, something valuable enough for the East Empire Company to hide from everyone.
Finally! Someone who believes me.

Node.Caption: DLC2RR03CresciusIntroExtBranchTopic06b: I admit, this does sound suspicious.

Cell.Text: Sigh. I don't care what you, or anyone else thinks about me.
Look, my wife nags that I'm too old to go traipsing around these mines chasing my story. | Time's my enemy... it's caught up with me before I could find the answers that I'm looking for.

Node.Caption: DLC2RR03CresciusIntroLastBranchTopic: Why are you telling me all of this?

Cell.Text: I do. I want to know what happened to Gratian, and what the East Empire Company is keeping from all of us.

Node.Caption: DLC2RR03CresciusIntroLastBranchTopic01: So you do need my help.

Cell.Text: [S] Gratian kept a journal of notes about his discoveries. If you can find his... remains, I'm hoping it will help. | Here's everything I have. The letter, the key. Please, do this for me so I can finally regain the respect that I've lost.

Node.Caption: DLC2RR03CresciusIntroLastBranchTopic02: Any idea of where to start?
